1.2: Enumeration for the possible ways to generate list genders.

GenderInfo provides a method to determine the gender of a list/array of objects when one knows the gender of each item of the list. It does this in a locale sensitive manner. The constructor initializes the object based on the locale data from the current goog.labs.i18n.ListFormatSymbols.

Similar to the ICU4J class com.icu.util.GenderInfo: http://icu-project.org/apiref/icu4j/com/ibm/icu/util/GenderInfo.html

Determines the overal gender of a list based on the gender of all the list items, in a locale-aware way.
An array of genders, will give the gender of the list.
